On November 22, 1978, Teddy Kennedy was alone with his thoughts in Arlington National Cemetery, at the gravesite of his older brother, who had been struck down this very day 15 years earlier.
His brow was furrowed, pushing down on his eyes, which were half shut and held dark shadows in their recesses.
